    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I can confirm a similar behavior when refining the results. For me, it almost always jumps back to default unrefined results. Is that the same for you? My `searchClient` is properly defined outside the component. \r\n\r\nUsing the `react-instantsearch-router-nextjs` like so: \r\n```typescript\r\n<InstantSearch\r\n      searchClient={searchClient}\r\n      indexName={index}\r\n      insights={false}\r\n      future={{\r\n        preserveSharedStateOnUnmount: true,\r\n      }}\r\n      routing={{\r\n        router: createInstantSearchRouterNext({ singletonRouter }),\r\n      }}\r\n    >\r\n      <SearchView />\r\n</InstantSearch>\r\n```",
